description:
Twenty Years of Drought - The Return of Botswana's Boteti River | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'The Creepy & Bizarre World of the Okavango Delta' here: https://youtu.be/5MDwmdS_V14

For 20 years the Boteti River in northern Botswana has not flowed. What was once an expansive and prolific body of water gradually dried up, leaving zebras, hippos, elephants and crocodiles dependent on the few pools formed from the occasional rains.
But now, for the first time in 30 years, rain has fallen in sufficient quantities hundreds of miles to the north in the Angolan highlands, sending a stream of water through the river bed. After years of extreme drought, the river has finally returned in all its glory, transforming the landscape.
